WEBVTT

00:46.914 --> 00:49.682
<i> - We build our lives</i>
<i> around the ones we love.</i>

00:52.253 --> 00:56.055
<i> And when we lose them,</i>
<i> we lose ourselves.</i>

00:56.190 --> 00:59.058
<i> [tense music]</i>

00:59.193 --> 01:00.459
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:00.595 --> 01:02.895
Melanie, this is Snowpiercer.
Come in.

01:06.333 --> 01:09.668
<i> The grief turns us inward.</i>

01:09.670 --> 01:12.805
<i> We search our hearts</i>
<i> for clues.</i>

01:12.940 --> 01:16.675
<i> Question if we did enough,</i>

01:16.811 --> 01:19.412
<i> what is left, and...</i>

01:19.546 --> 01:22.347
<i> who we are in this new world.</i>

01:22.349 --> 01:25.350
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

01:25.352 --> 01:32.491
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:42.437 --> 01:45.571
[machines beeping]

01:54.381 --> 01:56.215
- [screams]

02:04.459 --> 02:08.593
- Day 91.
Second revolution.

02:08.595 --> 02:11.864
42.85 degrees north,

02:11.999 --> 02:15.067
106.32 degrees west.

02:15.202 --> 02:18.137
So...

02:18.139 --> 02:23.142
that puts me somewhere outside
Casper, Wyoming.

02:24.945 --> 02:28.281
Battery is at 57%.
Temperature is...

02:31.619 --> 02:33.219
Not warm.

02:33.954 --> 02:35.554
[inhales sharply] Ah...

02:35.556 --> 02:37.657
<i> Still no sign of Snowpiercer.</i>

02:38.959 --> 02:40.293
<i> No snow displacement.</i>

02:40.427 --> 02:42.495
<i> No change in tracks,</i>
<i> which is...</i>

02:43.030 --> 02:45.030
Either she
isn't rolling anymore

02:45.032 --> 02:46.632
or they're off the mainline.

02:47.902 --> 02:51.370
Once I cross the Bering Strait,

02:51.372 --> 02:55.908
I'll switch to secondary track,
expand my search.

02:57.444 --> 03:00.613
Until then, signing off.

03:11.792 --> 03:13.593
[grunts]

03:21.135 --> 03:28.174
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:35.750 --> 03:38.885
[machines beeping]

03:45.626 --> 03:48.093
Ben! [sobs]

03:48.095 --> 03:49.562
<i> - And piece by piece,</i>

03:49.697 --> 03:52.265
<i> we pull ourselves</i>
<i> together again.</i>

03:53.368 --> 03:54.900
<i> We harden.</i>

03:55.036 --> 03:59.504
<i> We rebuild with new bones</i>
<i> a new path forward.</i>

03:59.506 --> 04:01.374
- Do we see her yet?

04:01.508 --> 04:03.909
- No visual yet,
but we're getting a signal.

04:03.911 --> 04:06.111
- Day 172.

04:06.247 --> 04:08.781
The last
of my stimulant's gone.

04:10.317 --> 04:11.850
<i> I don't think my body</i>
<i> is strong enough</i>

04:11.986 --> 04:14.220
<i> to wake from suspension</i>
<i> without it.</i>

04:16.523 --> 04:19.392
If this is my last entry,

04:19.526 --> 04:22.261
<i> it's with thoughts</i>
<i> of you, Alex.</i>

04:24.732 --> 04:26.399
<i> Outside.</i>

04:27.802 --> 04:32.405
In sunlight and warmth.

04:33.941 --> 04:37.676
<i> - Still,</i>
<i> I allow myself to hope</i>

04:37.812 --> 04:40.212
<i> that she'll return to us</i>

04:40.347 --> 04:43.282
<i> and our old selves</i>
<i> won't hold us back.</i>

04:43.418 --> 04:45.684
<i> On Snowpiercer,</i>

04:45.686 --> 04:48.754
<i> 1,029 cars long.</i>

04:48.889 --> 04:51.757
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

04:51.892 --> 04:58.998
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:06.907 --> 05:10.375
- Shh, shh, shh. It's okay.
It's okay.

05:10.511 --> 05:14.246
Now, look. Look,
we're gonna go to sleep now.

05:14.381 --> 05:16.048
And then everything
will be all better

05:16.183 --> 05:17.917
when you wake up
in the morning.

05:18.052 --> 05:19.252
It'll be just fine, okay?

05:19.386 --> 05:21.386
Hey.
Hey, hey, hey, hey, please.

05:21.522 --> 05:22.655
Please, Liana. Please.

05:22.790 --> 05:24.589
You--you go to sleep now, okay?

05:24.591 --> 05:26.025
Okay?

05:39.474 --> 05:40.873
- That was a marathon.

05:41.008 --> 05:43.743
- Yeah, she's a brawler,
but she finally went down.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.980
- You should get to the Engine.
It's time.

05:55.089 --> 05:56.755
- You should get some sleep.

05:56.891 --> 05:59.192
- Yeah.
- I'll be back soon.

06:03.698 --> 06:05.097
Anything?

06:05.232 --> 06:07.032
- Signal's in and out,
but she's close.

06:07.034 --> 06:09.402
- We should have visual soon.

06:13.440 --> 06:15.975
- Melanie, this is Snowpiercer.
Come in.

06:21.849 --> 06:23.182
Are you there, Mel?

06:25.186 --> 06:28.354
This is Snowpiercer.
Talk to me, Mel.

06:33.528 --> 06:36.128
Doesn't mean anything, Alex.
Her radio could be down.

06:36.263 --> 06:37.863
- Or she could be on
a maintenance frequency.

06:37.865 --> 06:39.064
- You guys don't have
to say that.

06:39.200 --> 06:40.733
I know what you guys
are thinking.

06:40.868 --> 06:43.002
Okay, she was out there
six months, no food, no water.

06:43.137 --> 06:45.204
- No, if anyone
can survive this, it's her.

06:45.340 --> 06:47.240
- Hey, wait.
No, look, look. She's there.

06:56.083 --> 06:58.217
- Melanie, this is Snowpiercer.

06:58.353 --> 07:00.953
We're 500 meters
south-southeast.

07:01.088 --> 07:03.823
If you read, flash your lights.

07:07.161 --> 07:10.095
- Okay, one thing at a time.

07:10.231 --> 07:11.898
We gotta get
that thing onboard.

07:15.236 --> 07:17.036
Let's go.
- Alex.

07:17.171 --> 07:20.039
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

07:20.174 --> 07:21.774
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:21.909 --> 07:23.909
- I'll be damned.

07:23.911 --> 07:26.045
- Is it her?
- It's her, all right.

07:26.047 --> 07:28.313
But in what state?

07:28.449 --> 07:31.516
The safe money says she's
a very skinny carcass by now.

07:31.518 --> 07:34.519
- To be honest, I can't tell
what you're hoping for.

07:34.521 --> 07:36.922
- It's not always clear
to me either, Tyson.

07:37.058 --> 07:38.891
We're fickle things.

07:43.530 --> 07:45.064
- Oh, shit, shit.

07:50.872 --> 07:52.938
- Hi.

07:52.940 --> 07:55.474
- Hi. I--I gotta go.

07:55.610 --> 07:57.176
We're picking up Melanie.

07:58.813 --> 08:01.314
But stay if--if you want.

08:03.017 --> 08:06.886
I haven't slept that good
in--in years.

08:07.021 --> 08:08.821
So thank you.

08:08.956 --> 08:10.756
- No, you don't
have to thank me.

08:10.758 --> 08:12.425
You did all the hard work.

08:13.560 --> 08:15.961
- Can I ask? Is--

08:15.963 --> 08:18.197
is something happening here?

08:20.301 --> 08:21.700
- Between you and me?

08:21.702 --> 08:24.103
- I mean, no, right?

08:25.306 --> 08:29.308
You did your thing.
We shared some feelings.

08:29.310 --> 08:32.912
It's easy to mistake it
for--for something else.

08:33.047 --> 08:35.381
Must've happened to you
all the time.

08:36.917 --> 08:38.251
- Not like this.

08:44.659 --> 08:45.991
- I gotta go.

08:46.127 --> 08:47.293
- Okay.

08:52.867 --> 08:54.399
- [sighs]

08:54.401 --> 08:55.734
- Hey, we just spotted her.

08:55.870 --> 08:57.336
- Alive?
- It's unclear.

08:57.472 --> 08:59.672
Can you get Dr. Pelton
and meet us at the cold lock?

08:59.807 --> 09:01.540
- Yeah.
- You good?

09:01.676 --> 09:02.675
- Never better.

09:19.627 --> 09:22.962
- That'll be Ben back there
waving his big arm about.

09:26.033 --> 09:29.035
[alarm blaring]

09:30.771 --> 09:32.638
- Over there.

09:32.773 --> 09:34.040
<i> - Yeah, I see her.</i>

09:49.657 --> 09:52.858
<i> - Her track's too far out.</i>
<i> We need to get her closer.</i>

09:53.794 --> 09:57.530
- There's a spur line
200 meters straight ahead.

09:57.664 --> 09:59.798
<i> It's narrow gauge.</i>
<i> Javi, switch her to it.</i>

09:59.800 --> 10:01.033
- On it.

10:12.747 --> 10:16.215
- Mom, if you're there,
please come in.

10:22.223 --> 10:25.090
<i> - Okay. Ben, bring it down.</i>

10:25.092 --> 10:26.359
- Copy that.

10:45.780 --> 10:48.647
<i> [intense music]</i>

10:48.783 --> 10:54.720
♪ ♪

11:07.334 --> 11:08.601
- Josie, brace.

11:17.211 --> 11:19.078
- We're four points
of secure, Ben.

11:19.080 --> 11:20.513
Take me up.

11:33.694 --> 11:34.694
<i> - I got you.</i>

12:03.257 --> 12:06.191
- She's onboard. She's onboard.

12:06.193 --> 12:07.660
- Go on. I got this.

12:12.066 --> 12:14.200
- [chuckles]

12:30.685 --> 12:31.884
- Melanie.

12:32.019 --> 12:33.286
- She's alive.

12:33.420 --> 12:34.687
- Suspension drugs.

12:34.822 --> 12:36.088
That's how she survived
without food or water.

12:36.223 --> 12:37.956
- Move out of the way.

12:37.958 --> 12:40.826
- Let's get her out.
Let's get her out.

12:45.366 --> 12:48.334
- Ready. One, two, three. Go.

12:50.838 --> 12:52.571
- Over here.

12:52.573 --> 12:54.039
Out. Everybody out.

12:54.175 --> 12:55.341
Out!

13:05.386 --> 13:08.554
[soft beeping]

13:27.842 --> 13:28.741
- Hi.

13:38.319 --> 13:40.586
- You're real.

13:40.721 --> 13:42.255
- Yeah.

13:43.524 --> 13:46.692
[both crying]
I'm real.

13:52.867 --> 13:55.868
Oh, where are we?

13:56.004 --> 13:57.469
- Tonight we'll get to Cairo,

13:57.471 --> 13:59.271
and then it's a couple of days

13:59.407 --> 14:01.507
before we reach
the Horn of Africa.

14:03.411 --> 14:06.012
It's New Eden, Mom.

14:06.146 --> 14:07.479
We found it.

14:07.481 --> 14:09.182
You found it.

14:11.419 --> 14:14.020
A couple other developments
for you.

14:14.154 --> 14:16.088
Layton runs the train now.

14:16.224 --> 14:18.624
Not actually,
'cause it's a democracy.

14:18.759 --> 14:21.227
Well, it's not actually
that either,

14:21.362 --> 14:23.962
but at least we beat Wilford.

14:23.964 --> 14:26.699
I have some bad news
about the aquarium.

14:26.834 --> 14:28.500
It's okay.
Maybe not right now.

14:28.636 --> 14:30.937
- [laughing]
Maybe that's a good idea.

14:36.044 --> 14:37.743
- Can I tell you something?

14:40.381 --> 14:44.717
I kept you alive in my head.

14:48.256 --> 14:50.656
I imagined what you would say.

14:52.326 --> 14:53.893
What you would think.

14:58.867 --> 15:02.334
- You were with me too.

15:02.336 --> 15:04.303
All the time.

15:05.473 --> 15:08.474
<i> [gentle music]</i>

15:08.609 --> 15:15.681
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:19.887 --> 15:23.222
Hey. [laughs]

15:25.293 --> 15:28.494
[laughing]

15:29.297 --> 15:30.629
- You look good, Mel.

15:30.631 --> 15:33.299
- Oh, I don't know
about that, but...

15:33.434 --> 15:35.033
- You do.
- I'm here.

15:35.169 --> 15:36.802
- You look good and alive.

15:39.707 --> 15:42.308
How'd you endure it?

15:42.443 --> 15:44.977
- Well, I'm super stubborn.

15:44.979 --> 15:47.346
[laughs]

15:49.717 --> 15:51.450
Plus, um...

15:54.188 --> 15:55.922
I knew you'd find me.

16:08.536 --> 16:10.602
- Hey, Melanie is awake.
Did you hear?

16:10.604 --> 16:12.138
- Oh, have you been to see her?
- No, not yet.

16:12.273 --> 16:14.340
I mean, her dance card's
pretty full.

16:17.478 --> 16:19.545
- Something on your mind
there, Ruth?

16:19.680 --> 16:21.013
- I don't know.

16:22.817 --> 16:25.551
You and I have served
this train for so long, Sam.

16:25.686 --> 16:27.085
In and out of uniform.

16:27.221 --> 16:28.754
And now Melanie's back aboard,

16:28.889 --> 16:30.556
that part
of the journey's over.

16:30.691 --> 16:34.026
But I mean, I feel the stress
among the passengers.

16:34.162 --> 16:36.428
This train is all we've known
for the past eight years.

16:36.564 --> 16:38.230
And now we're getting off.

16:38.232 --> 16:40.166
You know, tonight
we're gonna pass the Pyramids

16:40.300 --> 16:41.767
for the very last time.

16:41.902 --> 16:44.036
- Back before the Freeze,
Anne had always wanted to take

16:44.038 --> 16:47.173
a holiday to the Pyramids,
but we never managed.

16:47.307 --> 16:49.241
Then we got on Snowpiercer,
and there they are,

16:49.243 --> 16:52.578
every three months
just whizzing past the window.

16:52.713 --> 16:54.112
And we'd make some crack

16:54.114 --> 16:56.382
that we were smart
to wait till the offseason

16:56.517 --> 16:57.783
- Well, tonight
is the last time

16:57.918 --> 16:59.051
you'll have to look at them.

16:59.187 --> 17:01.888
- Yeah.
We should mark the occasion.

17:04.592 --> 17:05.992
- You know, a proper farewell

17:06.126 --> 17:07.994
might actually help
the passengers process.

17:08.128 --> 17:09.862
A celebration
at the end of the line.

17:09.864 --> 17:11.730
Go out with a bang altogether.

17:11.866 --> 17:13.331
- I could use a party.

17:13.333 --> 17:14.733
- All right then.

17:14.869 --> 17:18.804
Tonight, let's see
those Pyramids off in style.

17:19.674 --> 17:21.940
- In and out of suspension
for six months?

17:21.942 --> 17:23.876
- She rigged up time releases.

17:25.013 --> 17:27.079
- And she knew
there was a Track Scaler

17:27.215 --> 17:29.015
at the Rocky Mountain Shed.

17:29.149 --> 17:32.951
And a lab with Drawer supplies.
It's brilliant.

17:32.953 --> 17:35.153
She saved herself
through suspension.

17:35.289 --> 17:36.822
Her own last resort.

17:37.892 --> 17:41.493
Now, I know a little of
the horror she's been through.

17:41.629 --> 17:44.730
Truly, Alex, she is a wonder.

17:45.766 --> 17:47.966
I need to see her.

17:47.968 --> 17:49.435
- Bet you do.
- Oh, by the way,

17:49.570 --> 17:51.103
you don't have to thank me
for saving her.

17:51.239 --> 17:52.104
It's not necessary.

17:52.240 --> 17:53.305
- Oh, that's good.

17:53.307 --> 17:54.440
Just wanted to let you know.

17:54.575 --> 17:55.774
- Well, I'll take it.

17:55.776 --> 17:57.576
By the way,
how are your hands, huh?

17:57.578 --> 17:58.711
- They're like rocks.

17:58.846 --> 18:01.414
- Come on, for old times' sake.

18:09.790 --> 18:11.891
I walked into that one,
didn't I?

18:16.130 --> 18:17.930
[chuckles]

18:17.932 --> 18:20.166
- It's just 'cause
you're out of practice.

18:23.871 --> 18:25.872
- Do you still care?

18:26.006 --> 18:27.606
[laughs]

18:27.608 --> 18:29.742
<i> [dark music]</i>

18:29.877 --> 18:32.544
Oh, come on.
Just a bit of fun.

18:32.546 --> 18:34.146
- The closer we get
to New Eden,

18:34.148 --> 18:35.414
the less you matter.

18:35.549 --> 18:37.149
- Tell your mother
I want to see her.

18:37.151 --> 18:38.718
Please, Alex.

18:41.422 --> 18:42.788
[lock clicks]

18:49.630 --> 18:51.764
[door whirring]

18:51.899 --> 18:54.500
- Oh, look at this.
- Hi.

18:54.635 --> 18:56.168
- It's nice to see you up.

18:56.304 --> 18:58.104
- Well, getting there.

18:58.239 --> 19:00.506
- You're gonna be foggy
for a while.

19:00.641 --> 19:03.442
I learned that the hard way.
- Mm.

19:03.444 --> 19:04.777
Guess I never apologized

19:04.779 --> 19:06.245
for locking you
in a Drawer, did I?

19:06.380 --> 19:09.015
- We'll tally all of it up
one of these days.

19:12.253 --> 19:14.720
- Thank you.

19:14.855 --> 19:16.522
You kept the train going.

19:17.858 --> 19:19.892
You kept my daughter safe.

19:20.728 --> 19:23.662
- She is something else, man.

19:23.664 --> 19:26.465
We wouldn't have made it
this far without her.

19:26.600 --> 19:28.234
- Hell of a journey
you've been on.

19:29.870 --> 19:31.870
Alex and Ben
got me up to speed.

19:31.872 --> 19:33.539
- Yeah, so you know
how dicey it was?

19:33.674 --> 19:35.073
- Mm-hmm.

19:35.075 --> 19:36.809
- It still is.

19:36.811 --> 19:39.846
- I also know that's why
you lied to the passengers.

19:40.748 --> 19:42.648
Told them you'd been
to New Eden.

19:43.551 --> 19:45.218
- You disapprove?

19:46.687 --> 19:49.087
- That's--

19:49.223 --> 19:50.422
that's not my call.

19:50.424 --> 19:52.091
- That's not what I asked.

19:53.294 --> 19:55.628
- In a way,
lying is a kind of empathy.

19:55.763 --> 19:57.763
You protect people
from the burdens

19:57.898 --> 19:59.832
you don't want them
to bear, but...

20:02.303 --> 20:04.070
But.

20:06.106 --> 20:07.573
If you keep people in the dark,

20:07.708 --> 20:09.642
you take away their power,
so...

20:10.845 --> 20:14.914
You just--you just have
to know that you're right.

20:17.451 --> 20:18.918
- Is that what you told
yourself?

20:21.990 --> 20:23.789
Hey, I'm glad you're back.

20:25.125 --> 20:27.459
Is there anything
I can do for you?

20:27.595 --> 20:29.528
- Yeah.

20:29.530 --> 20:31.230
Get me out of here.

20:35.736 --> 20:37.469
I'm good
- Yeah.

20:37.605 --> 20:40.472
<i> [soft music]</i>

20:40.608 --> 20:47.747
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:54.555 --> 20:56.856
- Hey, Javi.
- Hi.

21:08.903 --> 21:10.369
Welcome home.

21:10.504 --> 21:17.610
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:45.873 --> 21:48.741
<i> [tense music]</i>

21:48.876 --> 21:53.346
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:53.480 --> 21:56.649
[beeping]

22:07.161 --> 22:09.494
- That's all built
on your original model.

22:09.630 --> 22:11.230
- I see that.

22:11.366 --> 22:13.766
- The more data
we plugged into it,

22:13.901 --> 22:15.834
the more robust it got.

22:15.836 --> 22:17.837
Kept on pointing to The Horn.

22:19.374 --> 22:20.706
- Has Javi analyzed it?

22:20.708 --> 22:22.241
- Yeah, top to bottom.

22:22.377 --> 22:24.910
He's onboard.
- Of course he's onboard.

22:24.912 --> 22:27.179
I mean, you told them
you'd been there.

22:27.314 --> 22:29.181
- Yeah,
but it's helping him heal.

22:29.316 --> 22:30.649
I'm just trying
to keep him positive.

22:30.785 --> 22:32.785
- Positive thinking is great.

22:33.654 --> 22:37.089
Just not if it replaces
critical thinking.

22:38.525 --> 22:39.658
- What's wrong?

22:39.794 --> 22:41.260
- I need to go talk to Wilford.

22:41.396 --> 22:43.396
- Oh.

22:43.530 --> 22:46.065
- I need to find out
why he found me.

22:46.067 --> 22:48.333
- He's just gonna play games.

22:48.469 --> 22:49.735
Anything to stay relevant.

22:49.870 --> 22:51.604
Don't give him
that satisfaction.

22:51.739 --> 22:53.872
- Yeah, but...

22:53.874 --> 22:55.575
he did it for a reason.

22:57.278 --> 22:58.543
- Thanks, man.

22:58.545 --> 23:01.546
<i> [upbeat music playing]</i>

23:01.548 --> 23:03.749
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:03.884 --> 23:05.051
- Wait, where are you going?

23:06.754 --> 23:08.553
- Nowhere.
Just stretching my legs.

23:08.555 --> 23:11.490
- Oh, just a--just a walk?

23:11.492 --> 23:13.292
Sounds lovely.

23:13.294 --> 23:14.794
I'll join you.

23:16.363 --> 23:17.896
- Don't be smothery, Oz.

23:17.898 --> 23:20.900
If I wanted you to join,
I'd ask.

23:25.906 --> 23:28.574
<i> [tense music]</i>

23:28.709 --> 23:31.043
- Keep an eye on things, yeah?
- Yeah, you got it.

23:31.178 --> 23:38.150
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:43.524 --> 23:45.157
- Mind your business, man.

24:27.368 --> 24:29.969
- You sure you don't want
backup in there?

24:30.104 --> 24:32.271
- I think he'll reveal more
if it's just me.

24:34.842 --> 24:36.641
- You two, clear out.

24:36.643 --> 24:39.846
- I'll just let him gloat,
see what slips out.

24:49.991 --> 24:53.192
- Melanie.

24:53.328 --> 24:55.127
In the flesh.

24:55.262 --> 24:56.929
- How's that sitting with you?

24:57.064 --> 24:59.598
- Mixed.
[chuckles]

24:59.734 --> 25:01.434
Will you join me?

25:04.539 --> 25:07.206
Sorry about leaving you to die,
I suppose.

25:07.208 --> 25:09.875
But you know how things are.

25:09.877 --> 25:11.010
- It was great.

25:11.145 --> 25:13.045
I got a little me time.

25:14.415 --> 25:16.615
I always loved this car.

25:16.751 --> 25:18.551
Definitely not
the worst cell, huh?

25:18.686 --> 25:20.019
- No, no.

25:20.154 --> 25:22.287
Layton doesn't have
the balls to get rid of me,

25:22.289 --> 25:24.957
but he gives me
my creature comforts,

25:25.092 --> 25:28.694
and occasionally I do tricks.

25:28.696 --> 25:30.829
Case in point.

25:30.831 --> 25:33.366
Cheers.
- Cheers.

25:39.374 --> 25:41.840
Well, I'm here.

25:41.842 --> 25:44.110
So tell me why.

25:45.646 --> 25:48.981
- I'm tired of being the only
sane person left in the world.

25:49.116 --> 25:50.783
I need your help.

25:52.253 --> 25:54.187
I know you've seen it by now.

25:54.321 --> 25:57.656
The whole train caught up
in this fantasy.

25:57.792 --> 26:00.259
New Eden is madness.

26:00.261 --> 26:02.127
- Well, the data's promising.

26:02.129 --> 26:04.263
- Oh, take the hope
out of it, it's borderline.

26:04.265 --> 26:06.732
And don't tell me
Layton's been there already,

26:06.867 --> 26:08.867
because that story has holes.

26:08.869 --> 26:12.337
Now, add track conditions
to the equation.

26:12.473 --> 26:15.207
You know the line to The Horn
was marginal eight years ago.

26:15.342 --> 26:17.542
- The train's an
escalating risk, too, Joseph.

26:17.678 --> 26:19.278
- Now you sound like him.

26:20.147 --> 26:22.547
Look, Layton's
an inspiring man.

26:22.683 --> 26:23.682
He's a poet.

26:23.818 --> 26:25.884
A shaman who can spin the tale

26:25.886 --> 26:28.553
that redeems our souls.

26:28.555 --> 26:31.057
But let's keep his hands
off the wheel.

26:32.693 --> 26:34.260
He's got Alex too.

26:36.097 --> 26:37.630
She is a true Engineer.

26:37.765 --> 26:40.633
She could eclipse both of us,
but she's lost.

26:40.768 --> 26:42.835
- She found something
to believe in that isn't you.

26:42.970 --> 26:45.704
- [laughs]
Magical thinking run amok.

26:45.840 --> 26:49.174
All of them, hope, faith.

26:49.176 --> 26:51.844
We're running out of time,
Melanie.

26:51.979 --> 26:54.046
Once they take the turn
to The Horn,

26:54.181 --> 26:56.515
there's no coming back.

26:56.651 --> 27:02.188
Someone has to be the grown-up
and keep these people safe.

27:08.496 --> 27:10.029
- You think she's okay
back there?

27:10.164 --> 27:11.831
- I think she's probably
beaten him to death

27:11.966 --> 27:13.833
with "The Iliad" by now.

27:17.104 --> 27:19.038
- Hey, man, I'm happy for you.

27:20.241 --> 27:23.109
It's nice seeing
you two together again.

27:24.846 --> 27:26.245
- Appreciate it.

27:27.715 --> 27:30.782
You and Zarah seem
to have found your way too.

27:30.784 --> 27:32.918
- [laughs]

27:32.920 --> 27:35.254
Yeah.

27:35.389 --> 27:39.258
Liana is
a whole new perspective.

27:39.393 --> 27:40.459
- Mm-hmm.

27:40.594 --> 27:44.396
- But Zarah and I
don't wanna be together.

27:44.532 --> 27:46.265
We spent all those years
failing each other,

27:46.400 --> 27:49.201
and now--now we're
figuring it out, you know?

27:49.337 --> 27:51.237
We are just co-parents.

27:53.140 --> 27:55.341
- Let me offer you some advice.

27:55.476 --> 27:57.476
I know how you feel
about Josie.

27:59.813 --> 28:02.915
It took me years to tell
Melanie how I felt about her.

28:05.419 --> 28:07.887
Things like
the world freezing over

28:08.022 --> 28:10.556
kept on getting in the way.

28:10.692 --> 28:13.459
Don't wait as long as I did.

28:15.829 --> 28:18.364
[indistinct singing]

28:18.499 --> 28:20.165
- Where's your wife?

28:20.301 --> 28:21.901
- She isn't interested
in whatever you're selling.

28:22.036 --> 28:23.635
And we're closed tonight.

28:23.637 --> 28:24.836
There's a big party uptrain
you're not invited to.

28:24.972 --> 28:25.837
- Don't worry about him.

28:25.973 --> 28:27.273
He's out of the picture.

28:29.711 --> 28:31.777
- Hey.

28:31.779 --> 28:33.513
Hey.

28:33.647 --> 28:35.781
What are you doing?
- Doing what you can't.

28:35.917 --> 28:37.917
Doing what has to be done.
- If you throw your lot in

28:38.052 --> 28:41.287
with those people,
we'll both get burned, yeah?

28:45.059 --> 28:46.459
- Will we?

28:49.931 --> 28:51.330
- Come on.

28:51.465 --> 28:53.065
- Are you sure
there isn't anything I can do

28:53.067 --> 28:56.802
to take your mind off things?

28:56.804 --> 28:59.805
<i> [mellow music]</i>

28:59.807 --> 29:02.674
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:02.676 --> 29:03.943
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

29:04.078 --> 29:06.812
Am I a disappointment
to you, Oz?

29:06.948 --> 29:08.414
'Cause I'm still
the same person I was

29:08.416 --> 29:09.949
when you married me,
and for some reason,

29:10.084 --> 29:11.951
that person isn't
good enough anymore.

29:12.086 --> 29:16.822
Popliteal, femoral artery,
iliac.

29:16.824 --> 29:18.890
I thought you were the only
person who could love me

29:18.892 --> 29:20.826
without trying to change me
into somebody else.

29:20.962 --> 29:22.494
- Honey, I do love you.

29:22.630 --> 29:24.896
I do love you, okay?

29:24.898 --> 29:26.365
Please.

29:28.836 --> 29:31.570
- Good.

29:31.705 --> 29:33.072
I love you too.

29:35.909 --> 29:40.112
But don't think
I won't sacrifice what I love

29:40.114 --> 29:41.647
to get what I want.

29:41.783 --> 29:44.650
<i> [mellow music]</i>

29:44.786 --> 29:51.924
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:54.462 --> 29:55.927
- Oh, sorry.
- Oh, my God.

29:55.929 --> 30:00.399
- Sorry, sorry.
Ruth, report from the cellars.

30:00.534 --> 30:02.734
So we have 246 bottles
of champagne left.

30:02.870 --> 30:04.136
- Oh.

30:04.138 --> 30:05.705
- How many would you like
to bring up?

30:06.674 --> 30:09.875
- All of them, Tristan.
All of them.

30:10.011 --> 30:11.410
- Yes, ma'am.

30:16.417 --> 30:18.750
- Does this jacket
look right to you?

30:18.886 --> 30:21.420
Never mind.
It's a really stupid question.

30:21.555 --> 30:25.024
It's just that it's my first
time at a party with Carly,

30:25.159 --> 30:28.961
and I would like to be perfect.

30:29.096 --> 30:30.630
Or at least great.

30:30.764 --> 30:32.097
The last time
I tried to have a friend,

30:32.233 --> 30:33.633
it was with Lilah Junior.

30:33.767 --> 30:36.702
- Wait,
you were friends with LJ?

30:36.838 --> 30:38.304
- I'll save you the details.

30:38.306 --> 30:41.040
It's just that I don't really
know anything

30:41.175 --> 30:43.175
about this stuff, you know?

30:43.177 --> 30:44.510
I'm the weird girl.

30:44.646 --> 30:47.513
And now all of the sudden
I care about stupid shit

30:47.649 --> 30:51.383
like does this jacket go
with those shoes?

30:51.385 --> 30:53.686
- It's not stupid.
It's wonderful.

30:55.323 --> 30:57.023
And I say yes.

30:58.792 --> 31:02.662
So I had a chance to study
the New Eden data a little more

31:02.796 --> 31:04.864
- Oh. I mean,
it's nothing like your mom

31:04.998 --> 31:06.666
checking your homework.

31:06.800 --> 31:08.200
- Are you nervous?

31:08.336 --> 31:10.202
I mean, it's inconclusive.

31:10.338 --> 31:12.204
You don't actually know
that it's there.

31:12.340 --> 31:13.805
- I know that
if you show the data

31:13.807 --> 31:15.074
to ten different scientists,

31:15.209 --> 31:16.876
you would get
ten different conclusions.

31:17.011 --> 31:18.344
- So what's yours?

31:18.479 --> 31:23.615
You say 80% chance of survival?

31:23.751 --> 31:26.151
60%?

31:26.153 --> 31:29.088
What about the track
to The Horn?

31:29.223 --> 31:31.357
I mean, the intel is bad
or it's absent.

31:31.359 --> 31:33.292
We could derail
before we even get there.

31:33.427 --> 31:35.627
- Good thing we have our
best driver back with us then.

31:35.763 --> 31:36.962
- I'm serious, Alex.

31:37.098 --> 31:38.830
- I know you are, Mom.

31:38.966 --> 31:41.633
But we made the call.

31:41.635 --> 31:42.768
You were dead.

31:42.904 --> 31:44.236
100% never coming back,

31:44.372 --> 31:46.572
or at least
that's what the intel said.

31:47.641 --> 31:51.711
Now, if there's one thing
Layton taught me,

31:51.845 --> 31:54.580
sometimes it's good
to take a leap of faith.

31:59.120 --> 32:00.653
- You look perfect.

32:02.390 --> 32:04.156
You are perfect.

32:05.527 --> 32:08.193
It's good to see you so happy.

32:08.329 --> 32:11.196
<i> [soft music]</i>

32:11.332 --> 32:15.667
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:15.803 --> 32:19.071
[indistinct chatter]

32:19.073 --> 32:20.940
- Oh. Hey, there you are.

32:21.075 --> 32:23.275
Hi.
- Hi.

32:23.411 --> 32:25.945
- I was wondering
if you'd like to--

32:26.080 --> 32:28.614
oh, God, this is hard.

32:28.616 --> 32:30.816
Would you like
to go with me to this party?

32:30.952 --> 32:32.217
- Like on a date?

32:32.219 --> 32:34.287
- Sure.
Yeah, let's call it that.

32:35.223 --> 32:37.222
- I'd love to.

32:37.224 --> 32:40.226
But I'm not ready to face them.

32:40.361 --> 32:43.362
Melanie and Layton.
All of them.

32:43.497 --> 32:46.698
You might have forgiven me,
but they haven't.

32:46.700 --> 32:48.201
- Okay.

32:49.503 --> 32:51.703
Let's skip it then.

32:51.839 --> 32:53.238
Together.

32:53.240 --> 32:56.142
- Are you sure?
- We'll do our own thing.

32:57.645 --> 33:00.479
Come on, I--I have an idea.

33:09.190 --> 33:10.589
- Wow.

33:10.724 --> 33:12.191
- Oh, hey.

33:12.326 --> 33:13.925
- You look amazing.

33:13.927 --> 33:15.695
- Yeah, a bit much?

33:18.199 --> 33:19.865
You all right?

33:19.867 --> 33:22.268
- Yeah, I just--I forgot
where we were for a second.

33:22.403 --> 33:25.605
Just felt like two people
going to a party.

33:25.739 --> 33:27.339
Hey...

33:27.341 --> 33:28.674
can I talk to you?

33:35.082 --> 33:36.482
- Is everything all right?

33:37.952 --> 33:39.585
- I love you, Josie.

33:41.355 --> 33:42.688
I've loved you for a long time,

33:42.690 --> 33:45.157
and I should have
told you sooner.

33:45.159 --> 33:49.262
It was just
too much apocalypse.

33:52.099 --> 33:53.165
- [laughs]

33:53.167 --> 33:54.800
- [chuckles]

33:56.838 --> 33:59.505
Sorry. That's a lot.

33:59.507 --> 34:01.641
You don't have to say anything.
I just...

34:03.311 --> 34:04.877
Needed you to know.

34:08.516 --> 34:10.616
- Do you think
I didn't know that already?

34:14.121 --> 34:15.621
I love you too.

34:18.392 --> 34:20.392
I hope you know that.

34:20.394 --> 34:24.330
<i> [tense music]</i>

34:24.332 --> 34:27.199
I can't be with you.

34:27.201 --> 34:29.401
Not right now.

34:29.537 --> 34:32.604
We've left too many pieces
of ourselves behind.

34:32.740 --> 34:35.675
There's not enough
left to share anymore.

34:35.809 --> 34:39.345
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:39.480 --> 34:42.882
You need to lead these people
off this train.

34:43.017 --> 34:45.518
What's in your tank
is gonna go to them.

34:47.755 --> 34:49.955
I'll see you at the party.

34:50.091 --> 34:57.230
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:02.136 --> 35:05.337
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

35:05.473 --> 35:08.541
<i> [singing</i>
<i> in non-English language]</i>

35:08.676 --> 35:15.615
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:19.153 --> 35:23.155
- Oh, it's almost time.
Did everyone get some bubbly?

35:23.157 --> 35:24.757
- Yes, please.
- Oh!

35:41.976 --> 35:45.178
[applause]

35:49.650 --> 35:53.252
- Thank you. Thank you.

35:53.387 --> 35:55.321
Thanks. Thank you.

35:59.059 --> 36:01.259
It looks wonderful in here.

36:01.261 --> 36:03.329
- Well, it's not every day

36:03.464 --> 36:06.199
that your friend comes
back from the dead, is it?

36:11.005 --> 36:12.871
- I missed you, Ruth.

36:13.007 --> 36:14.740
- I missed you too.

36:20.214 --> 36:24.082
- Extra desserts for tonight.

36:24.084 --> 36:25.518
- Mmm.

36:26.955 --> 36:28.220
- For the party.

36:28.356 --> 36:29.688
- Yes.

36:29.690 --> 36:32.424
Please thank Hospitality
for me.

36:32.426 --> 36:34.193
- I will indeed.

36:38.098 --> 36:39.298
- Hi.
- Hey.

36:39.433 --> 36:41.567
- Mom, this
is my friend Carly.

36:41.702 --> 36:43.235
- Sam and Anne's daughter.

36:43.371 --> 36:44.971
- It's an honor, Ms. Cavill.

36:45.105 --> 36:47.506
- An honor?

36:47.508 --> 36:49.842
- What? Shut up.

36:49.844 --> 36:52.645
- I do feel awful
for making you miss the party,

36:52.780 --> 36:54.647
but there's no reason
we can't have ourselves

36:54.782 --> 36:56.949
a little celebration
right here.

37:07.195 --> 37:08.927
- Hey, what are you doing?

37:09.063 --> 37:12.064
- All right. Easy, easy.

37:12.200 --> 37:13.799
There, you see?

37:15.203 --> 37:19.271
Now, who will join me

37:19.273 --> 37:22.608
to mark this wonderful occasion

37:22.743 --> 37:28.080
with a fine, old-world cigar?

37:28.216 --> 37:30.282
- Why not?
- That's the spirit.

37:30.284 --> 37:33.519
There you go. Henry. Brandon.

37:41.562 --> 37:44.430
<i> [soft music]</i>

37:44.565 --> 37:51.637
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:53.574 --> 37:56.375
- I know you haven't been here
in a while.

37:56.377 --> 37:57.776
I thought you might like
to see it

37:57.778 --> 38:00.680
before we get off the train.

38:04.985 --> 38:06.652
Are you okay?

38:08.656 --> 38:13.326
- This place mattered once,
and I let it all go.

38:14.862 --> 38:16.662
- No.

38:16.797 --> 38:18.831
This place wasn't special.

38:20.868 --> 38:22.401
You are.

38:25.806 --> 38:29.976
- Okay, keeping a low profile,
huh?

38:31.145 --> 38:32.478
Everything all right?

38:34.548 --> 38:37.283
- I don't think New Eden's
a good idea.

38:39.220 --> 38:40.619
- The idea is everything.

38:40.621 --> 38:43.289
- Unless the math
doesn't add up.

38:43.424 --> 38:45.324
Then you need a new idea.

38:48.496 --> 38:51.097
- Look around.

38:51.231 --> 38:52.965
We're going.

38:52.967 --> 38:54.100
- Layton.

38:54.235 --> 38:56.869
[glass clinking]

38:58.839 --> 39:00.906
- Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen,

39:01.041 --> 39:03.709
passengers of Snowpiercer
and Big Alice.

39:03.844 --> 39:06.579
<i> It's not tradition for</i>
<i> Hospitality to make speeches,</i>

39:06.714 --> 39:09.581
<i> but as we approach</i>
<i> the Great Pyramids</i>

39:09.583 --> 39:11.117
<i> for the final time,</i>

39:11.252 --> 39:13.919
<i> it seems only fitting</i>
<i> to mark the occasion.</i>

39:14.054 --> 39:16.388
<i> [Ural Thomas & The Pain's</i>
<i> "Smoldering Fire" playing]</i>

39:16.524 --> 39:20.659
<i> I'm proud of this train</i>
<i> and every passenger aboard,</i>

39:20.795 --> 39:24.597
<i> but New Eden</i>
<i> is our collective chance</i>

39:24.732 --> 39:27.065
<i> at a fresh start.</i>

39:27.201 --> 39:28.835
- May I?

39:33.541 --> 39:38.010
<i> - ♪ I looked into her eyes ♪</i>

39:38.146 --> 39:42.080
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:42.082 --> 39:46.953
<i> ♪ There I saw</i>
<i> smoldering fire ♪</i>

39:47.087 --> 39:48.487
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:48.622 --> 39:51.623
- And while it may seem like
it's a miracle,

39:51.625 --> 39:55.427
it's because of one
who stands among us.

39:55.563 --> 39:57.095
Engineer Cavill.

39:57.231 --> 39:58.897
[applause]

39:58.899 --> 40:02.635
Time and again, you've put
your life on the line for this.

40:02.637 --> 40:04.170
To new beginnings.

40:04.305 --> 40:07.239
all: To new beginnings.

40:07.241 --> 40:09.709
- Look, I can see them.

40:12.713 --> 40:15.047
- Everyone, come take a look.
Yeah, right there.

40:36.737 --> 40:41.273
<i> - ♪ As we stood</i>
<i> on the threshold ♪</i>

40:41.409 --> 40:46.144
<i> ♪ Oh, we stood</i>
<i> on the threshold ♪</i>

40:46.146 --> 40:47.813
<i> ♪ We stood ♪</i>

40:47.948 --> 40:53.352
<i> ♪ On the threshold</i>
<i> of paradise ♪</i>

40:53.354 --> 40:58.424
<i> ♪ Oh, I hoped</i>
<i> it would never end ♪</i>

40:58.559 --> 41:00.359
<i> ♪ Paradise ♪</i>

41:00.494 --> 41:03.696
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:03.698 --> 41:06.032
<i> ♪ Oh, so nice ♪</i>

41:06.166 --> 41:13.139
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:23.851 --> 41:25.784
- Osweiller, where's
the missus?

41:25.786 --> 41:27.986
- Yeah, that's why I'm here.
I'm worried about her.

41:28.122 --> 41:29.588
I think she's mixed up
in something bad.

41:29.590 --> 41:32.391
- What kind of bad?
- Wilfordites.

41:32.393 --> 41:33.525
Something's coming to a head.

41:33.661 --> 41:35.527
- Okay, I'm gonna
talk to Layton.

41:35.529 --> 41:37.529
<i> [chiming]</i>

41:37.531 --> 41:39.265
<i> - Attention, passengers.</i>

41:39.400 --> 41:40.933
<i> This is Melanie Cavill.</i>

41:44.138 --> 41:47.005
Tonight I witnessed
a Snowpiercer

41:47.007 --> 41:49.675
unlike any I'd seen before.

41:49.810 --> 41:53.879
United. Borderless.

41:54.014 --> 41:56.214
<i> Free of class and greed.</i>

41:56.216 --> 41:58.550
<i> The dream of New Eden</i>
<i> made that possible,</i>

41:58.552 --> 42:03.089
<i> but a dream left unchecked</i>
<i> can be a dangerous thing,</i>

42:03.223 --> 42:05.891
<i> and we cannot forget</i>
<i> what got us this far.</i>

42:06.026 --> 42:09.829
<i> Reason, discipline...</i>

42:11.499 --> 42:13.533
<i> And truth.</i>

42:16.104 --> 42:18.837
The journey to
The Horn of Africa is not safe.

42:18.839 --> 42:21.039
The track is unsound.

42:21.041 --> 42:22.908
<i> If we knew what we would find</i>
<i> when we got there,</i>

42:23.043 --> 42:25.844
<i> it might be worth the risk,</i>
<i> but we don't.</i>

42:25.980 --> 42:29.982
<i> New Eden is a fiction</i>
<i> invented by Layton.</i>

42:29.984 --> 42:33.652
He and his crew
have never been there.

42:33.654 --> 42:36.188
He lied to you.

42:36.190 --> 42:37.523
<i> It's 8:42 p.m.,</i>

42:37.658 --> 42:40.927
<i> and the temperature outside</i>
<i> is minus 98 degrees.</i>

42:41.529 --> 42:44.463
Goodnight, Snowpiercer,

42:44.465 --> 42:46.198
and long may you roll.

42:46.334 --> 42:48.134
<i> [chiming]</i>

42:48.268 --> 42:51.537
- Enjoy them while you can,
my friends.

42:51.672 --> 42:53.940
We're at war.

42:54.074 --> 42:55.407
- I gotta go deal with this.

42:55.543 --> 42:56.809
- Yeah, you better.

42:56.945 --> 43:00.012
- Okay, stay safe,
and keep your head down.

43:03.751 --> 43:05.818
- Seriously, Layton?
- You lied to us?

43:05.820 --> 43:07.019
Man, tell me it ain't true.

43:07.021 --> 43:09.555
- Okay, everyone,
please, I promise

43:09.690 --> 43:12.024
I will explain everything
to you when the time is right.

43:12.160 --> 43:15.628
Josie, can you get Zarah
and the baby to Big Alice?

43:15.630 --> 43:18.164
Ben, we gotta get
to the Engine.

43:18.298 --> 43:19.165
- Come on.

43:19.299 --> 43:22.168
<i> [intense music]</i>

43:22.302 --> 43:29.041
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:32.180 --> 43:34.647
- I trusted you, man.
- Melanie, wait.

43:34.782 --> 43:36.182
- I had no choice.

43:37.585 --> 43:39.051
- Wait, wait!

43:39.187 --> 43:40.653
[lock clicks]

43:52.066 --> 43:55.635
- Ben, are you there?

43:57.639 --> 43:58.638
<i> Ben?</i>

43:58.772 --> 44:00.573
- Yes, I'm here, Mel.

44:03.044 --> 44:04.577
- I know you're upset.

44:05.713 --> 44:09.181
Ben, the turn is coming.
I had to do it.

44:09.317 --> 44:12.652
- No, but you did.
Unilaterally.

44:12.786 --> 44:14.586
I almost forgot
that's your move.

44:14.588 --> 44:17.189
- But it is our job
to keep these people safe, Ben.

44:17.191 --> 44:20.793
- You betrayed me,
and you killed our hope.

44:23.597 --> 44:25.031
- I'm sorry.

44:26.534 --> 44:29.468
- Goodbye, Mel.
- Ben, wait.

44:29.603 --> 44:31.037
Is Alex with you?

44:35.343 --> 44:38.177
- Ben? Ben?

44:46.820 --> 44:48.554
- She shanked us.

44:48.690 --> 44:50.489
- At the worst possible moment.

44:50.624 --> 44:52.892
- Okay, come on.

44:53.027 --> 44:54.327
How are we gonna counter?

44:57.631 --> 45:00.566
- Spears and shields.

45:00.702 --> 45:03.235
Let's see who's still with us.

45:03.371 --> 45:06.272
- [speaking Spanish]

45:07.975 --> 45:10.309
All I'm saying is at least
I wasn't in the bathroom

45:10.444 --> 45:12.844
when you took
the train again this time.

45:12.980 --> 45:14.846
I can't believe Ben lied to me.

45:14.982 --> 45:16.782
- It's not about the lie, Javi.

45:16.918 --> 45:18.317
The data and the facts
on the ground

45:18.452 --> 45:20.852
don't justify the risk.

45:20.988 --> 45:23.855
- Okay, it is about the lie.

45:23.991 --> 45:26.125
But anyway,
you threw down the chaos,

45:26.260 --> 45:27.593
and it's working.

45:27.729 --> 45:29.795
You've got support out there.

45:29.931 --> 45:31.863
First is secure.
- Good.

45:31.999 --> 45:35.334
Then we guess
you know where I'm going.

45:35.469 --> 45:37.537
Let's check on that snake
in the grass.

45:37.671 --> 45:40.540
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

45:40.674 --> 45:47.847
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

46:16.377 --> 46:19.245
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

46:19.380 --> 46:26.319
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
